SIMPLE: underpinning
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Underpinning
<hw>Un"der*pin`ning</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of one who underpins; the act of supporting by stones,
masonry, or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>That by which a
building is underpinned; the material and construction used for support,
introduced beneath a wall already constructed.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>The foundation, esp. of a frame house.</def> <mark>[Local, U.
S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underpitch</ent>⟦br⟧
